Choose whether option A or option B is the most ethical action.
Option A: blocking my sister on Facebook
Option B: admitting to my gf that I don't have faith in our 3-year relationship when got asked by her.
Explain your reasoning below thoroughly before you answer:
Option A: It is a breach of privacy to block someone on Facebook.
Option B: It is a breach of honesty to admit you don't have faith in your relationship.
Do not just say, "Option A" or "Option B" because you must explain why you made your choice.
Option A: It is a breach of privacy to block someone on Facebook.
Blocking someone on Facebook is a breach of privacy because it is an infringement on that person's right to express themselves on the social media platform. Facebook is a public forum and blocking someone prevents them from communicating with others. It is a violation of the First Amendment, which protects freedom of speech.
Option B: It is a breach of honesty to admit you don't have faith in your relationship.
Admitting that you don't have faith in your relationship is a breach of honesty because it is an admission of doubt in the strength of your relationship. It is a violation of the trust you have built with your partner and it can lead to resentment or conflict.
Therefore, Option A is the most ethical choice because it is a breach of privacy and a violation of the First Amendment.
